# Landing — apps/landing

## Stack

Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, next-intl, next-themes, Tailwind v4, `@repo/ui`.

## Scope

- Marketing/public product pages only.
- Auth pages and OAuth callbacks live in `apps/dashboard`.
- CTA links use `NEXT_PUBLIC_DASHBOARD_URL`.
- Market data and catalog live in `apps/dashboard`; landing has no API fetchers.

## i18n

- Use next-intl with `localePrefix: 'never'`.
- Messages live in `src/messages/{ru,en}.json`; static imports via `src/i18n/messages.ts`.

## UI

- `LocaleSwitcher`, `ThemeToggle`, `PublicShell` остаются в landing (next-intl / next-themes / App Router) — намеренный split с dashboard.
- Import primitives from `@repo/ui` or `@repo/ui/components/...`.
- Import shared styles through `@repo/ui/globals.css`.
- shadcn CLI: run `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>` from `apps/landing`; primitives go to `packages/ui`, blocks to `src/components/`.
- `apps/landing/components.json` + `packages/ui/components.json` must stay in sync (`style`, `iconLibrary`, `baseColor`).
- Next.js keeps `postcss.config.mjs` with `@tailwindcss/postcss` for Tailwind v4.
- Prefer arrow functions for new React components, hooks, and helpers.
- Landing UI lives in `src/components/` grouped by domain (`layout`, `landing`, `locale-switcher`, `theme-toggle`, `ui`).
- Shared helpers: `src/lib/`, env: `src/config/`.
